---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Navbar from '../../components/Navbar.astro';
import Footer from '../../components/Footer.astro';

const frontmatter = {
  title: 'Three signs your operations need a reset',
  description: 'A simple audit of the friction points that slow delivery and drain energy.',
  category: 'Operations',
  tags: ['operations', 'efficiency'],
  readingTime: '4 min read',
};
---

<BaseLayout title={frontmatter.title} description={frontmatter.description} type="article">
  <Navbar />
  <main>
    <section class="section">
      <div class="container prose">
        <p class="eyebrow">{frontmatter.category}</p>
        <h1>{frontmatter.title}</h1>
        <div class="blog-meta">
          <span class="pill">{frontmatter.readingTime}</span>
          {frontmatter.tags.map((tag) => <span class="pill">#{tag}</span>)}
        </div>
        <p>Operational drag often appears as a series of small annoyances that slowly erode focus and speed.</p>
        <h2>1. Decisions are delayed</h2>
        <p>If every choice needs multiple approvals, the work will feel heavy. Clear ownership often solves a surprising amount of friction.</p>
        <h2>2. Hand-offs create confusion</h2>
        <p>Frequent context loss between teams is a strong sign that the system needs redesign rather than more effort.</p>
        <h2>3. People are over-functioning</h2>
        <p>When the team is constantly firefighting, a reset may be the fastest path to better results.</p>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>
  <Footer />
</BaseLayout>
